cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language comprehension and the use of language models to predict event-related potentials (ERPs) in EEG recordings. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of embeddings in the analysis could suggest a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the potential for further analysis of the model embeddings and their relationship to ERPs could suggest a fit with the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
